","m":"auspicious"},{"d":"रामस्य","m":"Rama's"},{"d":"जयशंसीनि","m":"signs of victory"},{"d":"निमित्तानि","m":"indications"},{"d":"बभूवुः","m":"appeared"}]},{"v":35,"dev":"निमित्तानि च सौम्यानिराघवःस्वजयायवै दृष्टवापरमसम्हृष्टोहतंमेने च रावणम् ।","trans":"Sri Rama was very delighted over the appearance of good signs of his own victory and thought 'Ravana is destroyed by me'.","words":[{"d":"स्वजयाय","m":"his own victory"},{"d":"सौम्यानि","m":"good"},{"d":"निमित्तानि","m":"indications"},{"d":"दृष्टवा","m":"seeing"},{"d":"परमसम्हृष्टः","m":"very delighted रावणम् Ravana"},{"d":"हतम्","m":"destroyed"},{"d":"मेने","m":"by me"}]}]}